Yellowstone  National  Park 	  Yellowstone National Park is in the northwestern corner of Wyoming. Although Yellowstone is best known for its incredible geysers, the park also has gorgeous mountain scenery and fantastic wildlife, including herds of amazing bison. The best known feature is Old Faithful, a geyser that’s not the highest, largest, or most beautiful, but is the most reliable. 
Southwest 	  The Southwestern United States is a great place to study geology. The region is so arid that in most locations rocks and structures are easily seen. In several concepts we will visit parts of the Southwest to view geology in the field. 
