Erratics 	  Rocks carried by a glacier are eventually dropped. These glacial erratics are noticeable because they are a different rock type from the surrounding bedrock. 
Yosemite  Valley is known for waterfalls 	  that plunge from hanging valleys. (a) A bowl-shaped cirque in Glacier National Park was carved by glaciers. (b) 
