Wasteful  Methods 	  Three popular irrigation methods are: • Overhead sprinklers. • Trench irrigation: canals carry water from a water source to the fields. • Flood irrigation: fields are flooded with water. All of these methods waste water. Between 15% and 36% percent of the water never reaches the crops because it evaporates or leaves the fields as runoff. Water that runs off a field often takes valuable soil with it. 
