Summary 	  • Neptune is so far from Earth that it can’t be seen without a telescope. • Neptune has a turbulent atmosphere, which changes the planet’s appearance. The blue color is due to frozen methane. • Neptune has 13 moons, including Triton, which orbits in the opposite direction from Neptune. 
