Summary 	  • Dark matter cannot be sensed by astronomers, but the effect of its gravity is seen on the motion of nearby objects. • Dark matter may be a combination of WIMPs and MACHOs. • Dark energy is still hypothetical, but if it exists it could be a significant portion of the energy of the universe. 
